  "type": "npc",
  "status": "active",
  "description": "Lanhawk Talon-captain of the Redjess clutch; the campaign's recurring corsair.",
  "narrative": "Vael, mid-thirties, a deed-name she will not explain. Her home spire was stripped to a husk by Combine crews under a lawful Crown charter; she watched it go down through the Undermist with her mother's tether still knotted to the dock. She holds a grudge like an heirloom and a genuine grievance, and she has decided the lawful world owes her a living. VOICE: courteous before violence, never after. GM ARC: fight her twice, bargain with her once, and keep her alive - by Act 4, when the lanes start dying under everyone equally, she is the ally nobody wants and everybody needs. She honors shrine-ground, the bier-right, and ransom custom without exception. LEVERAGE: the Combine charter that doomed her spire is in the Quillate's deep stacks, and the PCs can find it.",
